- www.addic7ed.com -

10:01.543 --> 10:05.512
[Crickets chirping]

10:12.487 --> 10:14.955
[Printer whirring]

10:14.990 --> 10:17.391
[Cellphone beeps]

10:17.425 --> 10:18.993
[Dialing]

10:19.459 --> 10:21.026
[Ringing]

10:22.323 --> 10:23.120
KIM: <i> Hello.</i>

10:23.179 --> 10:24.854
<i>You've reached the
voicemail of Kim Wexler.</i>

10:24.909 --> 10:27.159
<i>Please leave me a message, and I'll
get back to you as soon as I can.</i>

10:27.659 --> 10:29.093
[ <i> Beep</i> ] It's me again.

10:29.127 --> 10:30.761
Look, I think I found something

10:30.796 --> 10:32.315
that could help get you outta there.

10:32.480 --> 10:35.058
I'm gonna make things right.

10:35.092 --> 10:36.960
Call me, would you?

10:36.994 --> 10:38.861
[Cellphone beeps]

10:38.896 --> 10:43.199
[Whirring continues]

10:43.233 --> 10:46.703
[Printer beeps]

10:46.737 --> 10:49.238
[Sighs]

10:55.746 --> 10:57.714
ERIN: Hi. Whoa!

10:57.748 --> 10:59.282
Sorry. I didn't mean to sneak up on you.

10:59.316 --> 11:00.817
[Sighs]

11:00.851 --> 11:03.120
- I just thought everyone was gone.
- Nope.

11:03.167 --> 11:04.668
I'm here late most nights.

11:04.702 --> 11:06.069
Ah.

11:06.104 --> 11:09.473
By the way, I noticed in your office...

11:09.507 --> 11:11.909
you threw away a soda can.

11:11.943 --> 11:13.911
You're going through my trash?

11:13.945 --> 11:15.345
No. [Chuckles]

11:15.380 --> 11:16.880
I was just dropping off
papers at lunchtime,

11:16.915 --> 11:18.982
and I happened to notice
it in your trash can.

11:19.017 --> 11:20.517
I fished it out, so it's fine.

11:20.551 --> 11:22.686
Office cans are for recyclable paper...

11:22.720 --> 11:24.421
there's a separate big can
in the kitchen for plastic,

11:24.455 --> 11:26.056
glass, and aluminum.

11:26.090 --> 11:28.158
We take our ecological footprint
pretty seriously here.

11:28.192 --> 11:29.826
- [Printer beeps]
- Okay, so, the big can

11:29.861 --> 11:32.496
is where I should throw
my empty Scotch bottles.

11:32.530 --> 11:34.731
[Chuckles] No, I-I get it.

11:34.766 --> 11:36.867
Go green.

11:36.901 --> 11:39.903
Good. Was there anything else?

11:39.938 --> 11:42.506
Yeah, one quick thing. I have the
brief you gave Cliff this morning...

11:42.540 --> 11:45.075
the Plaintiff's Opposition
to the Defendant's Motion?

11:45.109 --> 11:46.343
I have a few notes.

11:46.377 --> 11:48.111
I think they're pretty clear,

11:48.146 --> 11:50.580
but it's probably easier if we
just go over them together.

11:50.615 --> 11:52.082
Jesus. Th-Those are Cliff's?

11:52.116 --> 11:53.750
No, they're my notes.

11:53.785 --> 11:55.385
I'd love go to over them
now, if you have a minute.

11:55.420 --> 11:57.120
It looks worse than it is.

11:57.155 --> 11:59.423
It's... It's just that we have
a particular house style.

11:59.457 --> 12:00.924
Okay, no offense,

12:00.959 --> 12:02.926
but, uh, you're a second-year
associate, right?

12:02.961 --> 12:04.795
- Yep.
- And I came in as a fourth-year.

12:04.829 --> 12:06.363
That's right.

12:06.397 --> 12:10.467
So, why is a second-year
giving notes to a fourth-year?

12:10.501 --> 12:13.470
Well, like I said, I
know the house style.

12:14.572 --> 12:17.207
Does Cliff have you babysitting me?

12:17.241 --> 12:18.642
No.

12:18.676 --> 12:22.245
This is just one associate
helping another.

12:22.280 --> 12:24.982
Like here, the Roman numeral headings...

12:25.016 --> 12:26.583
we use all caps for those.

12:26.617 --> 12:29.119
And you indented them,
which is perfectly fine,

12:29.153 --> 12:30.754
but Cliff likes them centered.

12:30.788 --> 12:32.389
Oh, and before I forget,

12:32.423 --> 12:34.992
we put two spaces after a
period on all our documents.

12:35.026 --> 12:36.827
I know it seems like a minor thing,

12:36.861 --> 12:39.096
but really looks so much
cleaner on the page.

12:39.130 --> 12:40.831
You went a tad overboard
with the quotations.

12:40.865 --> 12:42.099
It's okay to present a quote

12:42.133 --> 12:43.433
from a controlling legal opinion,

12:43.468 --> 12:44.801
but when you use too many,

12:44.836 --> 12:46.136
it disrupts the flow of your argument,

12:46.170 --> 12:47.738
and it gives the impression

12:47.772 --> 12:49.306
you don't know how to write
an argument of your own.

12:49.340 --> 12:50.640
[Chuckling] And I'm sure you do, so...

12:50.675 --> 12:52.175
[Chuckles] You have a tendency

12:52.210 --> 12:54.611
to overuse the words
"clearly" and "obviously."

12:54.645 --> 12:56.847
Again, it's a matter
of personal opinion...

12:56.881 --> 12:59.082
I really appreciate this, Erin,

12:59.117 --> 13:01.451
but, uh, I was just on my way out.

13:01.486 --> 13:05.288
So, if we could continue this
first thing tomorrow morning...

13:05.323 --> 13:07.624
Well, I was thinking we
should just get 'er done now.

13:07.658 --> 13:08.959
No time like the present.

13:11.162 --> 13:12.763
Sure.

13:12.797 --> 13:15.332
Let's roll up our sleeves and
apply a little elbow grease.

13:15.366 --> 13:16.633
Great!

13:16.667 --> 13:18.335
So, I'm gonna get my favorite pen,

13:18.369 --> 13:21.304
and I will see you momentarily.

13:21.339 --> 13:26.977
You got it.

13:36.254 --> 13:38.355
[Sighs]

13:38.389 --> 13:42.459
[Door opens, closes]

13:42.493 --> 13:45.796
[Keys jingling]

13:45.830 --> 13:50.100
[Skrilla Jones'<i> "22 Car Garage"</i> plays]

13:58.509 --> 14:01.411
[Cellphone ringing, vibrating]

14:11.956 --> 14:14.191
Uh, Miss Wexler?

14:14.225 --> 14:16.393
You can call me Kim.

14:16.427 --> 14:19.463
