29:32.780 --> 29:34.747
[Song ends]

29:34.782 --> 29:39.185
[Indistinct conversation]

29:43.591 --> 29:47.327
[Cellphone ringing, vibrating]

29:57.397 --> 29:58.698
[Cellphone beeps]

29:58.764 --> 30:01.199
Kim Wexler. Hey. How are you, Paige?

30:01.233 --> 30:03.401
You did?

30:06.084 --> 30:08.619
That's... [Chuckles]
That's so nice to hear.

30:08.662 --> 30:10.697
I thought we hit it off, as well.

30:13.334 --> 30:15.401
Really?

30:15.436 --> 30:17.003
I...

30:17.037 --> 30:19.873
I, uh, I-I couldn't be more thrilled.

30:19.907 --> 30:23.109
It... I mean, the firm and I. [Chuckles]

30:24.232 --> 30:26.200
Absolutely. I'll tell him right now.

30:26.234 --> 30:29.003
I'm sure we can get something
on the books tomorrow...

30:29.037 --> 30:31.472
day after, at the latest.

30:31.506 --> 30:34.208
Thank <i> you,</i> [Chuckling] Paige.

30:34.242 --> 30:36.510
Me, too. Okay, bye.

30:36.544 --> 30:38.846
[Cellphone beeps]

30:42.651 --> 30:44.818
Yes!

30:44.853 --> 30:49.056
[Chuckles]

30:51.059 --> 30:56.664
â™ª

30:59.534 --> 31:04.271
[Indistinct conversations]

31:16.518 --> 31:19.286
[Clears throat]

31:23.224 --> 31:25.192
- There she is.
- [Chuckling] Hi.

31:25.226 --> 31:27.361
- Hi.
- Paige, so good to see you.

31:27.395 --> 31:28.662
You, too.

31:28.697 --> 31:30.497
Kim, this is Kevin Wachtell, our C.E.O.

31:30.532 --> 31:32.433
Kim Wexler. Great to meet you, Kevin.

31:32.467 --> 31:34.201
And you.

31:34.235 --> 31:35.936
Uh, Paige, Kevin, this is Howard
Hamlin, our senior partner.

31:35.971 --> 31:37.338
- Pleasure.
- Likewise.

31:37.372 --> 31:39.106
We're thrilled to have you folks here.

31:39.140 --> 31:41.375
Kevin, true story...
when I was 7 years old,

31:41.409 --> 31:43.677
my very first bank account
was at Mesa Verde,

31:43.712 --> 31:45.212
if you can believe it.

31:45.246 --> 31:47.614
I can. Mine was, too, back
when my dad ran the place.

31:47.649 --> 31:50.250
Wow. I can remember the
cover of my first passbook.

31:50.285 --> 31:51.852
It was a silhouette of a...

31:51.886 --> 31:53.554
Cowboy.

31:53.588 --> 31:56.056
Cowboy on horseback, yes,
standing next to a cactus.

31:56.091 --> 31:57.624
I loved that cowboy.

31:57.659 --> 31:59.893
Far as I was concerned, I was
saving up for that horse.

31:59.928 --> 32:02.863
What the heck else is money good
for when you're 7 years old?

32:02.897 --> 32:04.231
[Laughter]

32:04.265 --> 32:05.599
So, we have a little
presentation for you

32:05.633 --> 32:07.368
in our conference room,
along with some snacks

32:07.402 --> 32:09.269
and a soy mocha latte
with your name on it.

32:09.304 --> 32:10.537
Oh.

32:10.572 --> 32:12.072
This one... she's a keeper.

32:12.107 --> 32:13.474
Shall we?

32:13.508 --> 32:16.310
KEVIN: Let's do it.

32:16.344 --> 32:19.747
[Indistinct conversations]

32:25.920 --> 32:27.654
Well, I think that couldn't
have gone any better.

32:27.689 --> 32:29.790
- Pleasure to meet you.
- Fantastic. I'll see you soon.

32:29.824 --> 32:31.892
- Thanks for setting this up.
- Talk to you soon.

32:31.926 --> 32:33.160
[Vehicle door opens]

32:33.194 --> 32:34.762
HOWARD: Lovely to meet you, Paige.

32:38.133 --> 32:43.170
[Engine starts]

32:51.679 --> 32:52.980
Congratulations.

32:53.014 --> 32:54.782
Right back at you.

32:56.384 --> 32:59.253
I'll circle back with Paige,
get the ball rolling,

32:59.287 --> 33:01.288
start talking strategy, you know?

33:01.322 --> 33:03.991
Maybe... put together a
list of staff associates

33:04.025 --> 33:05.359
we can put on this.

33:05.393 --> 33:06.890
I'll put Francis on that.

33:07.796 --> 33:09.711
You've got enough on your
plate in doc review.

33:28.934 --> 33:31.302
[Knocking on door]

33:34.182 --> 33:35.950
Coming.

33:38.553 --> 33:39.753
Huh.

33:39.788 --> 33:41.021
Hey!

33:41.056 --> 33:42.256
HOWARD: Catch you at a bad time?

33:42.290 --> 33:45.659
Not at all. Come in.

33:45.694 --> 33:48.329
[Glass clinking]

33:48.363 --> 33:49.863
I hear clinking.

33:49.898 --> 33:53.167
Does that mean we have
something to celebrate?

33:53.201 --> 33:55.869
We sure do.

34:03.745 --> 34:06.013
What are we drinking to?

34:06.047 --> 34:08.282
Got a juicy one for you.

34:08.315 --> 34:10.617
- Mesa Verde?
- On retainer.

34:10.652 --> 34:13.353
[Chuckling] Oh, even better.

34:13.388 --> 34:14.888
[Chuckles]

34:14.922 --> 34:16.290
Congratulations.

34:16.324 --> 34:19.226
One of your golf-course conquests?

34:20.395 --> 34:22.629
Kim Wexler brought them in.

34:22.664 --> 34:24.598
Fourth-year associate snags

34:24.632 --> 34:26.967
a quarter of a million in billings?

34:27.002 --> 34:30.103
She's probably having a
couple of drinks herself.

34:30.138 --> 34:32.572
She's out of the doghouse, I assume?

34:33.641 --> 34:35.376
We'll see.

34:35.409 --> 34:37.978
Huh.

34:38.013 --> 34:39.413
Hmm.

34:39.447 --> 34:43.976
Interstate expansion...
it's a complex case.

34:44.181 --> 34:47.735
That's two, maybe three
regulatory commissions

34:47.782 --> 34:49.007
we'll be dealing with...

34:49.212 --> 34:53.047
months of work for HHM, maybe years.

35:04.127 --> 35:05.761
[Computers beeping]

35:07.597 --> 35:10.165
[Beeping]

35:12.001 --> 35:15.137
[Crickets chirping]

35:29.452 --> 35:31.953
[Engine shuts off]

35:31.988 --> 35:34.589
[Car door opens, closes]

35:37.160 --> 35:40.829
[Sighs]

35:44.267 --> 35:45.834
Good morning, Rudolpho.

35:45.868 --> 35:48.637
Good morning, Mr. McGill.

36:30.313 --> 36:33.048
Oh, sorry.

36:34.150 --> 36:35.350
[Chuck sighs]

36:35.384 --> 36:37.652
I didn't know anyone was here.

36:37.687 --> 36:40.355
Just dropping off some Sandpiper stuff.

36:40.389 --> 36:41.656
You're in early.

36:41.691 --> 36:44.493
More like late. [Clears throat]

36:46.329 --> 36:49.364
Well, regardless of the
hour, good to see you here.

36:49.398 --> 36:51.466
Yeah, I'm trying something new.

36:51.501 --> 36:53.668
I'm coming in, working until 9:00.

36:53.703 --> 36:55.971
It's easier before the place opens,

36:56.005 --> 36:59.307
without all the lights
and the phones ringing.

36:59.342 --> 37:00.542
[Chuckles]

37:00.576 --> 37:02.544
How about some coffee?

37:02.578 --> 37:03.979
No, thank you.

37:04.013 --> 37:06.815
W-Would you mind making me some?

37:06.849 --> 37:08.083
I apologize.

37:08.117 --> 37:11.153
It's just I-I can't do it myself,

37:11.187 --> 37:13.755
what with the electricity.

37:15.358 --> 37:16.892
Sure. No sugar.

37:16.926 --> 37:19.494
Um, just a splash of soy milk.

37:19.529 --> 37:22.831
I think we have it.

37:22.865 --> 37:25.000
Kim?

37:25.034 --> 37:29.204
Um, make two cups.

37:42.218 --> 37:43.585
[Sniffles]

37:43.619 --> 37:46.621
Well, I guess it's true what they say...

37:46.656 --> 37:51.426
the early bird gets the worm,
which is good if you like worms.

37:51.460 --> 37:53.728
- [Chuckles]
- [Chuckles]

37:53.763 --> 37:56.565
Mm. [Sniffles]

37:59.402 --> 38:01.369
May I ask you a question?

38:01.404 --> 38:02.604
Of course.

38:02.638 --> 38:05.173
Do I have a future at this firm?

38:07.777 --> 38:09.744
We have a lot in common, you and I.

38:09.779 --> 38:11.079
[Cup thumps lightly]

38:11.113 --> 38:13.081
My brother left you holding the bag.

38:13.115 --> 38:14.950
If it makes you feel any better,

38:14.984 --> 38:18.420
you're not the first person
to go out on a limb for him.

38:18.454 --> 38:22.657
I made the same mistake
over and over again.

38:22.692 --> 38:24.793
And now Howard has...

38:24.827 --> 38:26.661
and he blames you.

38:29.265 --> 38:33.435
It's a damned mess.

38:36.372 --> 38:39.641
Jimmy ever tell you
anything about our father?

38:39.675 --> 38:40.976
Not much, no.

38:41.010 --> 38:42.577
[Sighs]

38:42.612 --> 38:48.149
My dad... our dad... he was...

38:48.184 --> 38:54.589
well... the personification of good.

38:54.624 --> 38:59.194
I'm not sure he could
even see sin in any form,

38:59.228 --> 39:02.764
like he was born without the gene.

39:02.798 --> 39:05.300
He ran a little corner
store in Cicero...

39:05.334 --> 39:08.003
cigarettes behind the
counter, penny candy...

39:08.037 --> 39:11.806
nothing special, but it
kept food on the table.

39:11.841 --> 39:14.476
And the neighborhood loved Dad.

39:14.510 --> 39:16.778
He knew everybody's name,

39:16.812 --> 39:19.648
what was going on in their lives.

39:20.850 --> 39:25.253
This little corner... he made it better.

39:28.224 --> 39:30.058
I was named after him.

39:32.495 --> 39:35.030
Before that, he'd worked for a
lot of people over the years,

39:35.064 --> 39:38.233
and his dream was to be his own boss...

39:38.267 --> 39:41.836
put everything he had into that place.

39:41.871 --> 39:46.207
I was away at college when
he put Jimmy to work there.

39:46.242 --> 39:50.278
Jimmy grew up in that
store, watching our father.

39:52.882 --> 39:56.017
But Dad was not the world's
greatest businessman,

39:56.052 --> 39:58.853
and eventually, he ran
into money troubles.

39:58.888 --> 40:01.256
I, um, had a clerkship at the time,

40:01.290 --> 40:03.658
but I came home to help him
get his books in order,

40:03.693 --> 40:05.727
set the ship straight.

40:05.761 --> 40:07.862
Now, I'm no accountant,

40:07.897 --> 40:13.168
but I discovered $14,000 was just gone,

40:13.202 --> 40:16.805
vanished over the years.

40:18.908 --> 40:22.377
Turns out Jimmy had pilfered
it in dribs and drabs...

40:22.411 --> 40:24.546
just took it out of the till.

40:27.383 --> 40:30.919
My dad wouldn't hear it.

40:30.953 --> 40:34.122
Nope. Not his Jimmy.

40:37.326 --> 40:39.928
He ended up having to sell.

40:39.962 --> 40:42.764
Six months later, he was dead.

40:42.798 --> 40:48.937
At the funeral, no one
cried harder than Jimmy.

40:52.441 --> 40:57.879
My brother is not a bad person.

40:57.913 --> 41:01.783
He has a good heart.

41:01.817 --> 41:04.152
It's just...

41:06.355 --> 41:07.922
...he can't help himself.

41:09.492 --> 41:12.761
And everyone's left
picking up the pieces.

41:16.766 --> 41:18.500
Is there any coffee left?

41:18.534 --> 41:19.768
No, I got it.

41:19.802 --> 41:21.770
[Clears throat, sniffles]

41:25.174 --> 41:27.275
CHUCK: I'll talk to Howard,

41:27.309 --> 41:29.978
pour a little oil on troubled waters.

41:30.012 --> 41:32.847
You're being wasted down in doc review.

41:32.882 --> 41:34.883
Good job with Mesa Verde.

41:44.827 --> 41:48.163
[Indistinct conversations]

41:48.197 --> 41:50.465
[Bell dings]

41:50.499 --> 41:56.004
[Yvonne Devaney's <i>"The Girl Who
Finally Won"</i> plays in background]

41:59.542 --> 42:03.411
[Sighs]

42:17.660 --> 42:20.695
MAN: Mind if I join you?

42:22.264 --> 42:24.632
Hi.

42:24.667 --> 42:26.000
What can I get you?

42:26.035 --> 42:28.203
Coffee... black.

42:28.237 --> 42:31.506
Coming right up.

42:31.540 --> 42:33.408
[Sighs] Mm.

42:33.442 --> 42:37.579
He really did a number on you.

42:39.682 --> 42:43.818
Sorry. I know you?

42:43.853 --> 42:45.820
The young man who did that to you.

42:45.855 --> 42:49.424
He's my nephew...
hothead, always has been.

42:49.458 --> 42:51.759
Kid thinks he's a boxer.

42:51.794 --> 42:56.764
He should have shown you respect.

42:56.799 --> 43:02.871
I apologize to you on
behalf of my family.

43:05.541 --> 43:07.842
Apology accepted.

43:07.877 --> 43:10.245
And you know what?

43:10.279 --> 43:14.349
He should go to jail...
best thing for him.

43:14.383 --> 43:17.685
Teach him respect for his elders.

43:17.720 --> 43:21.856
But... not for eight years...

43:21.891 --> 43:26.861
less, much less.

43:26.896 --> 43:31.733
[Music continues]

43:42.645 --> 43:45.446
You see what I'm getting at?

43:45.481 --> 43:47.148
Not really.

43:47.182 --> 43:51.986
The gun charge... that's 8 years
he's going away, maybe 10.

43:52.021 --> 43:56.824
Aggravated assault, the gun,
plus he got your wallet.

43:56.859 --> 43:58.793
That's right.

43:58.827 --> 44:00.595
[Floyd Cramer's <i> "Losers
Weepers"</i> plays in background]

44:00.629 --> 44:06.167
I would like for you to tell the
police that the gun was yours.

44:06.201 --> 44:07.635
Would you?

44:07.670 --> 44:10.905
You're both a little
hot under the collar

44:10.940 --> 44:14.075
about whether you bumped his car or not.

44:14.109 --> 44:17.912
But there was a scuffle,
and, uh, he got your gun.

44:17.947 --> 44:19.314
My gun?

44:19.348 --> 44:22.150
Your gun from your pocket...

44:22.184 --> 44:26.487
he got it, and that's how
his prints got on it.

44:26.522 --> 44:29.691
And then I'd be subject
to the gun charge.

44:30.793 --> 44:32.961
You're an ex-cop.

44:32.995 --> 44:36.130
They'll go easy on you.

44:36.165 --> 44:38.533
So you're a psychic.

44:38.567 --> 44:43.938
I'll even twist Tuco's
ear, make him apologize.

44:43.973 --> 44:49.177
And he serves for battery...
nothing else.

44:52.581 --> 44:59.954
I'm looking for the best
possible outcome for everybody.

44:59.989 --> 45:03.558
And for your trouble...

45:03.592 --> 45:08.396
you take home $5,000.

45:12.401 --> 45:15.403
[Cup thumps lightly]

45:20.242 --> 45:22.844
Think about it.

45:33.222 --> 45:35.523
[Cup thumps lightly]

